A halin yanzu, kasar Sin ta gabatar da shirinta a shekarar da ta gabata: tana son zama ta daya a fannin kirkirar fasaha ta zamani nan da shekarar 2030.
"Karuwan kudaden da ake kashewa a kan binciken AI zai zama kyakkyawan farawa, tunda sauran kasashen sun fi Amurka baya, kuma muna neman babban ci gaban AI na gaba", in ji Lee.
"Komawa da kudaden da ake da su zai kara da cewa ci gaban AI na gaba zai kasance a Amurka", in ji Lee a wata hira da CNBC a wannan makon.
Lee, wanda littafinsa AI Superpowers: China, Silicon Valley and the New World order da Houghton Mifflin Harcourt ya wallafa a wannan watan, shi ne shugaban kamfanin Sinovation Ventures, wanda ya zuba jari a cikin wani kamfani na AI na kasar Sin mai suna Face++.
A cikin 1980s a Jami'ar Carnegie Mellon, ya yi aiki a kan tsarin AI wanda ya ci nasara da dan wasan American Othello da mafi yawan maki kuma daga baya ya kasance mai zartarwa a Microsoft Research na reshen Google na China.
Lee ya bayyana tsoffin gasar fasaha na gwamnatin Amurka a matsayin Ƙalubalen Robotics na Ƙungiyar Cibiyar Bincike ta Ƙaddamarwa ta Ƙaddamarwa kuma ya tambayi lokacin da zai kasance na gaba don taimakawa wajen gano masu hangen nesa.
A Amurka, masu bincike sukan yi aiki tukuru don samun tallafin gwamnati, in ji Lee.
"Kasar Sin ba ta janyo shugabannin ilimi ba, amma kamfanoni", in ji shi.
A cikin 'yan shekarun nan, Facebook da Google da sauran kamfanonin fasaha sun ɗauki ƙwararrun ƙwararru na jami'a don yin aiki a kan AI.
Lee ya nuna cewa sauya manufofin shige da fice na iya taimakawa Amurka don haɓaka ƙoƙarin AI.
"Ina ganin ya kamata su ba da katin zama ga likitocin IA", in ji shi.
Majalisar zartarwa ta kasar Sin ta wallafa shirinta na bunkasa fasahar kere kere ta zamani a watan Yuli na shekarar 2017.
